[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering environment variables**\n\nI’m thinking about how to handle the environment variables. If `JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS` is present, it could lead to unwanted output like \"Picked up\" if I don't manage things correctly. So, to avoid any confusion with child processes and stderr, I wonder if removing both variables in the helper function would be the right approach. It seems like a good plan to streamline the process and avoid those unnecessary prints.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d6c41d9c8c310e7016a2438c37ea88190a1bd07f08a7dcae1\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJDjngkFkjOFOi9aNwJQgXKihxTLsg_tNqHn4yXA2OBhSFuk70OrOT0u8hzpCKL6BRiiNzvnOd2BXxaMCS8_eJ_1rIeTDfFjja4mAztoxrFgS5fSNzQ-r5WhZWefk_Sit7QcxZ0pPvS3XDSGcFTnxWTVTBdI4fkr_zhA-drEcBU0a9iY_g1aWBfx8Q6slUQ0yNz7D3ZGBQuzJxakOZ4XNl1tZgTgBQ3uRLY6DmDo90bSciMKMPxsmfwDAXdloItAxNL2OH1c0gdPcnJAHICazocVvrG_SKtKa5G6abid1hWVwHxCiQZON_7r3aaCGKcVfpLE7pG3WSvC9qlGkECx6SoEVyHsXV7Sph25PPiieD_AuKw_ZxzY7NN9X4i_yWOcZhEOLu0OrKHT4Vz5qfuBDzBeJq3agtzqNC6n6xtyVZS7ggeO1umyOJfurhNaWEMOIX8Yo9KFPUoaGh8WKOCdveZ5Qv_-i07xXH5wQJ79FvXX-GNXiuNl0wuii4VAqXG-kzikmblpavrI-DBmxM9QT5sXAMN8YOBCd4cAUMPixrACaTGrywCLeRdj4ZPRzksgCxjMIHW7EjvbI9vBkLoe0b6iT2kVHm2LezZaqdsbMl_Z5KNwIJ7VA7zbNkdO_DmxsW-9F8GHX1LYao6_fZAUyOW1hj-_9takknw34WURn7pmLKmLMP0terOYaL4kf7kPnlLr2ZuNjwF3lFmURwlJgMyY4frK6oa2R5I7-2XvPYFjQtTXAnID5Jb8QY4myaoPXZWqAPQRMLNkYg5ih4XR494Gk66n8Xr4oR0YtIrpw1YL9qbnBLG_oJc0dvB_KDGHPY8li_NBzVz_5wIpt67iau8_tW5pXMsupH6gubbQorVBNZssRsxFS48y4YI-r-920Tkr4rApe1SasWum_pPSNNRS4rDWcU7GQ_gmXcD8iw3sdIQc4Z9-t6m-79k1gV1ilf5JiQO27PNR1-tpZecVtvfwKrzmcQ67KY2H6r4xwU_v72NXALn3Eh6uFf2ZWh4upvOeHK_6y8m_OK3tlqAronCZGL_5qIst52L_3YcytuDU-UtF9mM_E0itfPe-ijOh1TR-N47ziMRPEXDb_2kuqYsZ0esEpkRwB77-xFL0gozBt35s6xk-c2TzqgvQDsvjnMQOLNOANW9Sdmfv_-a4HxYeXO6lnxC9KGjOAwcAZAUsI51MGcc4K3hs9gO1XVENlO12Aa0O1-QFdOSiE4CXac_oWCHsB8Zt4ExeSupJaSG8i3q4FlaRwo2